                  "textEn": "For example, if a young person is struggling with academic pressure or emotional stress, talking to a teacher, a parent, or a close friend can be like throwing them a lifeline. That conversation may not solve everything overnight, but it can help them see the problem more clearly and feel less alone.",
                  "textZh": "例如,如果一個年輕人正為學業壓力或情緒困擾所苦,和老師、父母或親密朋友傾談,就像有人向他拋出一條救生索一樣。那次對話未必能一夜之間解決所有問題,但卻能幫助他更清楚地看見問題,也讓他不會覺得自己是孤軍作戰。",
