                  "number": 2,
                  "sourceNumber": 6,
                  "stage": "explanation",
                  "labelEn": "Explanation",
                  "labelZh": "解釋",
                  "sourceLabel": "Explanation 2",
                  "textEn": "If young people rely on others for every obstacle, they may never learn how to think for themselves or stay calm under pressure. Sometimes, struggling a little is part of growing up, because it forces people to find their feet and develop inner strength. In a way, challenges can act like a mirror: they show people what they are capable of when no one else can do the work for them.",
                  "textZh": "如果年輕人每遇到障礙都依賴別人,他們可能永遠學不會獨立思考,也學不會在壓力下保持冷靜。有時候,經歷一點掙扎其實正是成長的一部分,因為這會迫使人站穩腳步,培養內在的力量。某程度上,挑戰就像一面鏡子：當沒有人能替你完成事情時,它會讓你看見自己究竟有多大能力。",
