                  "labelZh": "解釋",
                  "sourceLabel": "Explanation",
                  "textEn": "If disagreements are handled badly, even a capable team can start to fall apart at the seams. People may stop listening to one another, become defensive, or focus more on proving a point than solving the problem. Once that happens, the team is no longer pulling in the same direction, and even small tasks can begin to feel like an uphill battle. In that sense, conflict can spread through a team like a crack in a wall: if it is ignored, it tends to widen over time.",
