                  "textEn": "If students are simply told to “work together”, the idea can remain vague. However, if one student is responsible for research, another for presentation, and another for organising the final work, they learn that teamwork is not just about sitting at the same table; it is about pulling their weight and working towards the same goal. In a way, clear roles act like the glue that holds the group together, because they prevent people from drifting or leaving everything to one person.",
