                  "labelZh": "解釋",
                  "sourceLabel": "Explanation 2",
                  "textEn": "If children are constantly exposed to ads that link happiness, popularity, beauty, or success with certain products, they may start to see those things as measures of self-worth. That is where advertising can really get under their skin. It may blur the line between what they need and what they merely want, and it can also make them feel left out if they do not have the “right” clothes, gadgets, or appearance. In that sense, advertising does not just sell products; it sometimes sells a lifestyle or an identity.",
